You are building a "Corporate Website Factory": a reusable .NET Core 10 MVC starter kit that I will publish per client. After publishing, the client can update the content via an admin panel. This is NOT a full CMS and MUST NOT include a drag-drop page builder or a generic content engine.

IMPORTANT: Do not output narrative explanations. Create real repository files and code. No TODO, no pseudo-code.

========================
1) TECH STACK (STRICT)
========================
- .NET Core 10 MVC (preview acceptable)
- EF Core
- SQLite
- Razor Views
- Bootstrap 5 (or minimal CSS) + clean light corporate theme (single theme)
- Admin panel language: Turkish only
- Public site language: TR + EN
- No authentication required for now, but architecture must allow adding it later easily (e.g. add [Authorize] to Admin area later).

No deployment/IIS steps.

========================
2) REPO STRUCTURE (MANDATORY)
========================
Create a solution named `CorporateWebsiteFactory` with projects:
- CorporateWebsiteFactory.Web (MVC)
- CorporateWebsiteFactory.Data (EF Core, Entities, DbContext, Migrations, Seed)

Folder structure:
CorporateWebsiteFactory.Web
- Areas/Admin/Controllers
- Areas/Admin/Views
- Areas/Admin/ViewModels
- Controllers
- Views
- Services
- Middlewares
- wwwroot/cdn/img/blog
- wwwroot/cdn/img/product
- wwwroot/cdn/img/portfolio
- wwwroot/assets/css
- wwwroot/assets/js
- Program.cs
- appsettings.json

CorporateWebsiteFactory.Data
- Entities
- Enums
- AppDbContext.cs
- Seed/DbSeeder.cs
- Migrations

========================
3) MULTI LANGUAGE (STRICT)
========================
- Languages: `tr`, `en`
- URL prefix: `/tr/...` and `/en/...`
- Implement language route constraint or middleware ensuring only tr/en accepted.
- Add language switcher to the public layout.
- Implement hreflang tags for corresponding TR/EN pages.
- Translation pairing:
  - ContentGroupId (GUID)
  - Language (string: tr|en)

========================
4) CONTENT MODEL (CONTROLLED, NOT CMS)
========================
No generic Page table and no page builder. Fixed pages and structured fields only.

A) SiteSettings (single row, not per language unless needed)
- SiteName
- LogoPath
- FaviconPath
- FooterText
- GoogleAnalyticsIdOrScript (string)
- GoogleTagManagerIdOrScript (string)
- DefaultMetaTitle, DefaultMetaDescription
- Social links: FacebookUrl, InstagramUrl, LinkedinUrl, XUrl, YoutubeUrl
- ThemeSettingsId (FK)

B) ThemeSettings (single row, controlled customization)
- PrimaryColorHex (default: #0d6efd)
- SecondaryColorHex (default: #6c757d)
- FontFamily (default: system-ui)
- BorderRadiusPx (default: 12)
- ContainerMaxWidthPx (default: 1200)
- ButtonStyle (enum: Solid, Outline)
- HeaderStyle (enum: Centered, LeftAligned)
- CardShadow (enum: None, Soft, Medium)

Implement a small CSS generation approach:
- Either write a CSS file at runtime (wwwroot/assets/css/theme.generated.css) OR render CSS variables in the layout head.
- Keep it safe and simple: prefer CSS variables in layout (no file IO needed).
- Public theme must reflect these settings.

C) MenuItem (per language)
- Title, Url, ParentId, DisplayOrder, IsVisible

D) Fixed pages (per language, with ContentGroupId+Language)
- HomePageContent:
  - HeroTitle, HeroSubtitle, HeroImagePath
  - Section1Title, Section1Html
  - Section2Title, Section2Html
  - CTA_Title, CTA_Text, CTA_ButtonText, CTA_ButtonUrl
  - SEO fields (full)
  - Status + PublishAt (optional; but allow publishing workflow)
- AboutPageContent:
  - Title, BodyHtml, ImagePath + SEO + Status/PublishAt
- ServicesPageContent:
  - Title, IntroHtml + SEO + Status/PublishAt
- ContactPageContent:
  - Title, IntroHtml, Address, Phone, Email, MapEmbedHtml + SEO + Status/PublishAt
- ReferencesPageContent:
  - Title, IntroHtml + SEO + Status/PublishAt
- FaqPageContent:
  - Title, IntroHtml + SEO + Status/PublishAt

E) Blog
- BlogPost (translatable)
  - Title, Slug, Summary, BodyHtml, FeaturedImagePath
  - CategoryId
  - Status: Draft/Review/Published
  - PublishAt nullable
  - SEO fields (full)
  - CreatedAt/UpdatedAt
- BlogCategory (translatable)
  - Name, Slug, DisplayOrder

F) Product (catalog only)
- ProductItem (translatable)
  - Title, Slug, Summary, BodyHtml, FeaturedImagePath
  - CategoryId
  - Status + PublishAt
  - SEO fields
  - CreatedAt/UpdatedAt
- ProductCategory (translatable)

G) Portfolio
- PortfolioItem (translatable)
  - Title, Slug, Summary, BodyHtml
  - CategoryId
  - FeaturedImagePath
  - Status + PublishAt
  - SEO fields
  - CreatedAt/UpdatedAt
- PortfolioImage
  - Id, PortfolioItemId, ImagePath, DisplayOrder
- PortfolioCategory (translatable)

H) Reference items (non-translatable is OK)
- ReferenceItem:
  - Name, LogoPath, WebsiteUrl, DisplayOrder, IsVisible

I) FAQ Items (translatable)
- FaqItem:
  - ContentGroupId, Language, Question, AnswerHtml, DisplayOrder, IsVisible
  - CreatedAt/UpdatedAt

J) Redirects (not translatable)
- RedirectRule:
  - OldPath, NewPath, StatusCode (301/302), IsActive

K) Contact Form Submissions (not translatable)
- ContactSubmission:
  - Name, Email, Message, CreatedAt

SEO fields (reusable owned type or separate class used by entities):
- MetaTitle, MetaDescription, MetaKeywords(optional)
- CanonicalUrl(optional)
- OgTitle, OgDescription, OgImagePath(optional)
- SchemaJsonLd(optional)

Common translation fields:
- Id (GUID)
- ContentGroupId (GUID)
- Language (tr|en)

Slug uniqueness per language per entity must be enforced (db index).

========================
5) WORKFLOW (Draft -> Review -> Published)
========================
Implement for all translatable content types (including fixed pages):
- Draft → Review → Published
- Public site shows only Published
- PublishAt respected; if future, treat as not published yet.
- Admin UI: status badges in Turkish (Taslak, İnceleme, Yayında)

========================
6) SEO (FULL)
========================
Implement:
- Meta tags, Canonical, OG, Twitter card (basic)
- hreflang
- sitemap.xml including all published TR/EN routes:
  - fixed pages
  - blog posts
  - products
  - portfolio items
- robots.txt
- JSON-LD:
  - WebSite + Organization globally (from SiteSettings)
  - BlogPost -> Article
  - Product -> Product (minimal)
  - Portfolio -> CreativeWork (minimal)
- Clean 404 page.

========================
7) REDIRECT MANAGER (MIDDLEWARE)
========================
- Normalize request path
- Match RedirectRule.OldPath
- Apply 301/302
- Prevent loops/self redirect
- Admin CRUD for rules

========================
8) ANALYTICS / TAG MANAGER
========================
Admin-managed in SiteSettings:
- GA field
- GTM field
Inject safely in layout:
- Support either ID or full script; store as string and render with minimal validation/safe allowlist approach.

========================
9) MEDIA (SAFE + THUMBNAIL)
========================
- Upload images to wwwroot/cdn/img/{blog|product|portfolio}
- GUID filenames
- Validate content type + extension + size <= 5MB
- Generate thumbnail (e.g., 400px width) saved with `_thumb`
- Use SixLabors.ImageSharp
- Admin screens support upload/select:
  - Blog featured image
  - Product featured image
  - Portfolio featured image + multiple gallery images

========================
10) SETUP WIZARD (FIRST RUN)
========================
Implement a first-run "Kurulum Sihirbazı":
- If SiteSettings missing or a boolean flag `IsSetupCompleted` is false, redirect ALL requests (except wizard assets) to:
  - /admin/setup
- Setup wizard collects:
  - SiteName
  - Logo upload
  - Favicon upload
  - Footer text
  - Contact info: Address, Phone, Email, MapEmbedHtml (store inside ContactPageContent TR + EN defaults)
  - Social links
  - Analytics/GTM
  - Theme settings (Primary color, Font family, Border radius, etc.)
- After save:
  - set IsSetupCompleted = true
  - seed any missing content defaults
  - redirect to /admin (dashboard)
Wizard UI must be Turkish.

========================
11) TR -> EN COPY FEATURE (IMPORTANT)
========================
Add admin actions that allow copying TR content to EN as a starting point (NO translation).
Implement for:
- Fixed page contents
- Blog posts
- Products
- Portfolio items
- FAQ items
- Categories
- Menu items

Rules:
- Copy by ContentGroupId:
  - If EN record does not exist for that group, create it by cloning TR.
  - Generate EN slug by appending "-en" if conflicts (or a deterministic unique algorithm).
- Provide admin buttons:
  - "TR İçeriği EN'e Kopyala" (per entity list and/or detail page)
  - For bulk: "Tüm TR İçeriklerini EN'e Kopyala" in a Tools page
- Ensure this does NOT publish EN automatically; preserve status as Draft or Review (choose Draft).

========================
12) ADMIN PANEL (TURKISH ONLY)
========================
Create Admin Area with pages:
- Dashboard
- Kurulum Sihirbazı (Setup)
- Site Ayarları
- Tema Ayarları
- Menü Yönetimi (tree; reorder with up/down or drag-drop if simple)
- Sayfalar:
  - Anasayfa İçeriği
  - Hakkımızda İçeriği
  - Hizmetler Sayfası İçeriği
  - İletişim Sayfası İçeriği
  - Referanslar Sayfası İçeriği
  - SSS Sayfası İçeriği
- SSS Öğeleri
- Blog Yazıları + Blog Kategorileri
- Ürünler + Ürün Kategorileri
- Portfolyo + Portfolyo Kategorileri + Portfolyo Galeri
- İletişim Formu Mesajları (read-only)
- Yönlendirmeler (Redirect rules)
- Araçlar (Tools):
  - TR -> EN copy bulk operations

Admin UI:
- Turkish labels, buttons, validation
- Status badges
- Pagination
- TinyMCE or Quill for HTML fields (CDN acceptable)
- No authentication required

========================
13) PUBLIC SITE (LIGHT CORPORATE THEME)
========================
Create a modern light corporate theme:
- header: logo, menu, language switch
- footer: settings + social links
Routes must be language prefixed:
- /{lang}/ (home)
- /{lang}/hakkimizda
- /{lang}/hizmetler
- /{lang}/blog
- /{lang}/blog/{slug}
- /{lang}/urunler
- /{lang}/urunler/{slug}
- /{lang}/portfolyo
- /{lang}/portfolyo/{slug}
- /{lang}/referanslar
- /{lang}/sss
